## 1. Definitions
- **Software** — the LUnA (logrok universal agent) binaries, packages, container
  images, and accompanying documentation distributed by Logiqum.
- **Core** — the free capability set the Software runs with **no license** (file
  tail, syslog-in, journald, HTTP-in, parsers, TLS syslog output, metrics).
- **Apex** — the paid capability set (incl. Windows Event Log, disk
  store-and-forward spool, central fleet management, edge reduction, per-agent
  mTLS, ack'd relay, Kubernetes container-log, macOS unified-log, UDP/data-diode
  output, experimental OS architectures).
- **Agent** — one running instance of the Software on one host. Counting is
  **per Agent, not per container or per source.**
- **Entitlement** — a Logiqum-signed grant (enrollment-derived from a licensed
  logrok deployment, or a standalone signed license file) that authorizes Apex
  for a stated tier, Agent count, and term.
- **Non-commercial use** — personal, educational, research, or evaluation use not
  undertaken for or in connection with commercial advantage or monetary
  compensation.

## 2. License grant
Subject to your compliance with this Agreement, Logiqum grants you a limited,
non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to install and run the
Software as follows:

- **2.1 Core — free.** You may run the Software's **Core** capabilities at no
  charge for: (a) **Non-commercial use**; (b) use **together with a validly
  licensed logrok deployment**; and (c) **commercial use up to 10 Agents** (the
  "free commercial floor"). Core has no Agent limit for (a) and (b).
- **2.2 Apex — requires an Entitlement.** Apex capabilities require a valid
  Entitlement — either issued automatically to an Agent enrolled with a licensed
  logrok deployment (**free with logrok**), or a **standalone commercial**
  Entitlement purchased from Logiqum. Your use of Apex is limited to the tier,
  Agent count, and term stated in your Entitlement or applicable order.
- **2.3 Grace and degradation.** When a paid Entitlement expires, Apex
  capabilities continue for a **grace period (default 30 days)**, after which the
  Software **degrades to Core** and continues running. The Software never ceases
  operating, and never grants more than Core without a valid Entitlement.

